## 5. Data Flow — Detailed

### 5.1 CCXT Ingestion Pipeline

{% mermaid
   code="sequenceDiagram\n    participant Beat as Celery Beat\n    participant CI as CcxtInitTask<br/>(hourly)\n    participant AL as AssetListingTask\n    participant EX as ExchangeTask<br/>(per exchange)\n    participant CCXT as Exchange APIs<br/>(Binance/Bybit/OKX…)\n    participant DB as TimescaleDB<br/>h1_data\n    participant Q as Redis Queue\n    participant CALC as CalcIndicatorsTask\n\n    Beat->>CI: trigger every 1h\n    CI->>AL: chain() — refresh asset listings first\n    AL->>CCXT: load_markets() × 8 exchanges\n    AL->>DB: INSERT new assets → asset_listing\n\n    AL-->>CI: listing complete\n    CI->>CI: getExchangeAssets()<br/>filter USDT/BTC/ETH pairs<br/>exclude leveraged tokens (2S/3S/UP/DOWN)\n    CI->>EX: group() — parallel dispatch per exchange\n\n    loop For each asset (up to 1000 per exchange)\n        EX->>CCXT: fetch_ohlcv(asset, \"1h\", limit=1000)\n        CCXT-->>EX: list of [ts, O, H, L, C, V]\n        EX->>EX: take second-to-last candle (closed candle)\n    end\n\n    EX->>DB: executemany INSERT INTO h1_data<br/>(asset, exchange, timestamp, O, H, L, C, V)\n    DB-->>EX: RETURNING last_id, asset\n\n    loop For each timeframe table [h1,h2,h4,h12,d1,d3,w1,m1]\n        EX->>Q: CalcIndicatorsTask.apply_async(table, [(id,asset)…])\n    end\n    Q->>CALC: dequeue\n" /%}

### 5.2 CoinGecko Market Data Pipeline

{% mermaid
   code="\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant Beat as Celery Beat\n    participant CGT as CoingeckoTask<br/>(every 30 min)\n    participant API as CoinGecko REST API\n    participant DB as TimescaleDB<br/>cg_data\n\n    Beat->>CGT: trigger every 30 min\n    loop Pages 1–8 (250 coins/page = 2000 total)\n        CGT->>API: GET /coins/markets?vs_currency=usd<br/>&order=market_cap_desc&per_page=250&page=N\n        API-->>CGT: JSON array of coin objects\n        Note over CGT: Retry with 30s backoff on failure\n    end\n\n    CGT->>CGT: Build DataFrame<br/>Parse ath_date, atl_date timestamps<br/>Compute days_since_ath<br/>Compute ATH proximity flags<br/>(ATH5, ATH10, ATH15, ATH>15)\n    CGT->>CGT: df.round(4)<br/>attach sys_timestamp (UTC)\n    CGT->>DB: executemany INSERT INTO cg_data<br/>(symbol, name, close, market_cap, rank,<br/>fdv, volume, high_24h, low_24h,<br/>price_change, ath, atl, flags…)\n" /%}

### 5.3 Technical Indicator Calculation Pipeline

{% mermaid
   code="sequenceDiagram\n    participant Q as Redis Queue\n    participant CI as CalcIndicatorsTask\n    participant DB as TimescaleDB\n    participant PD as Pandas / Pandas-TA\n\n    Q->>CI: (table_name, [(last_id, asset), …])\n\n    loop For each (last_id, asset) pair\n        CI->>DB: SELECT last_id, O, H, L, C, V<br/>FROM {table} WHERE asset=?<br/>AND timestamp ≤ candle_ts<br/>ORDER BY timestamp DESC LIMIT 300\n        DB-->>CI: up to 300 rows (reversed → chronological)\n\n        alt Quote currency ≠ USDT\n            CI->>DB: SELECT close FROM h1_data<br/>WHERE asset = quote+'/USDT'\n            DB-->>CI: close price for volume conversion\n        end\n\n        CI->>PD: calc_indicators(df)\n        Note over PD: EMA(10, 36, 200)<br/>SMA(200)<br/>EHMA(180) — custom Ehlers Hull<br/>RSI(14)<br/>BBands(20, std=2)<br/>TD Sequential (up/down counts)<br/>Supertrend(7, 3)<br/>Range%, HighLowRange%, VolumeUSD\n\n        PD-->>CI: enriched DataFrame\n        CI->>CI: extract last row → 28-column tuple\n        CI->>DB: INSERT INTO indicators<br/>(last_id, timeframe, ema200, diff_ema200,<br/>diff_ema200_pct, sma200, rsi14, bbands,<br/>ema36, ehma180, td_seq, st73, ema10,<br/>range_pct, volume_usd, …)\n    end\n\n    CI->>DB: COMMIT\n\n" /%}

### 5.4 Multi-Timeframe Continuous Aggregate Flow

{% mermaid
   code="flowchart TD\n    H1[(h1_data\\nHypertable\\n1h raw OHLCV)]\n\n    H1 -->|time_bucket 2h\\nContinuous Aggregate| H2[(h2_data)]\n    H1 -->|time_bucket 4h\\nContinuous Aggregate| H4[(h4_data)]\n    H1 -->|time_bucket 12h\\nContinuous Aggregate| H12[(h12_data)]\n    H1 -->|time_bucket 1 day\\nContinuous Aggregate| D1[(d1_data)]\n\n    D1 -->|time_bucket 3 days\\nContinuous Aggregate| D3[(d3_data)]\n    D1 -->|time_bucket 1 week\\nContinuous Aggregate| W1[(w1_data)]\n    D1 -->|time_bucket 1 month\\nContinuous Aggregate| M1[(m1_data)]\n\n    subgraph Aggregation[\"Each Continuous Aggregate computes\"]\n        AGG[\"LAST(last_id, timestamp) → last_id\nFIRST(open, timestamp) → open\nMAX(high) → high\nMIN(low) → low\nLAST(close, timestamp) → close\nSUM(volume) → volume\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph RefreshPolicies[\"Auto-Refresh Policies\"]\n        RP1[\"h2: every 2h\\nh4: every 4h\\nh12: every 12h\"]\n        RP2[\"d1: every 1 day\\nd3: every 1 day\\nw1: every 1 week\\nm1: every 4 months\"]\n    end\n" /%}

### 5.5 Database Cleanup Pipeline

{% mermaid
   code="flowchart LR\n    Beat[Celery Beat\\nWeekly trigger] --> DBC[DbCleanupTask]\n    DBC -->|DELETE stale indicators| IND[(indicators)]\n\n    subgraph Logic[\"Cleanup Logic (per timeframe)\"]\n        L1[\"Keep only the row with\\nmax(last_id) per\\n(asset, exchange, time_bucket)\\nfor the last 14 days\"]\n    end\n\n    DBC --- Logic" /%}

